{{Quote|I have studied the Kenobi offensive. It was masterful.|Gial Ackbar|<ref name="TTAB" />}}
[[File:ObiWan.png|thumb|General Kenobi, the creator of the Kenobi Offensive.]]
The '''Kenobi Offensive''', '''or Kenobi offensive''', was a series of [[Starship/Legends|starship]] maneuvers devised by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]]<ref name="TTABS">''[[The Truce at Bakura Sourcebook]]''</ref> during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="TCSWE KO">{{CSWECite|II|212|Kenobi Offensive}}</ref> It was a flexible attack plan intended for use by a small maneuverable force against a larger and better-armed blockading force. The scheme called for a series of sniping attacks, drawing a portion of a larger force out of formation. To keep the attacking force out of the enemy's firing arcs, vessels had to be reoriented constantly, but if done so successfully, at least one defending ship could typically be destroyed. This gap in the enemy defenses could then be exploited by the attacking force to destroy the enemy from inside their own formation, relying on the defending force to have difficulty returning fire at the risk of hitting their own vessels in such close quarters.<ref name="TTABS" />

Kenobi's attack plan was successful enough to be well known during the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Era]] and was studied by [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Gial Ackbar]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Fleet]].<ref name="TTABS" /> Ackbar found the Kenobi Offensive masterful<ref name="TTAB">''[[The Truce at Bakura]]''</ref> and sought to modify the maneuver for use by the Alliance against the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] during the [[Galactic Civil War]]. Ackbar included discussion and refinements of the Kenobi Offensive in his<ref name="TTABS" /> military guidebook ''[[Fleet Tactics and Combat Methodology|Fleet Tactics and and Combat Methodology]]'', which was intended for reading by Alliance naval officers.<ref name="TCSWE FTaCM">{{CSWECite|I|280|Fleet Tactics and Combat Methodology}}</ref>
[[File:AckbarHS-SWE.png|left|thumb|Admiral Ackbar modified the Kenobi Offensive for use by the Rebel Alliance fleet.]]
In this document, Ackbar noted how Rebel military doctrine was already basically the same as the general premise of the Kenobi Offensive: to draw the enemy out of position by moving where they least expect it and then attacking them from within. Ackbar contended that in order to minimize the Imperial fleet's communications advantage, that Alliance forces should seek to use natural or artificial means to achieve near total communications blackout for both sides during a battle, relying on an instituted code and line-of-sight system to take a lead in communications ability and speed over the enemy. As the Imperial Navy did not use such a system, having heretofore little need for one, Ackbar believed that the number of close Alliance victories could be appreciably increased.<ref name="TTABS" />

In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="Essential Reader's Companion">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] and Alliance pilot [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] informed Ackbar that General Kenobi's [[Force ghost/Legends|Force ghost]] had insisted that Skywalker be allowed to accompany the Alliance strike force being sent to the aid of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Bakura/Legends|Bakura]]. Ackbar mentioned his admiration for the Kenobi offensive while stating his trust in Kenobi's military knowledge and Luke's word. He explained that it was that trust that made him willing to acquiesce to the request.<ref name="TTAB" />

== Behind the scenes ==
The Kenobi offensive was first mentioned in [[Kathy Tyers]]' novel [[The Truce at Bakura|''The Truce at Bakura'']], which was published in [[1993]].<ref name="TTAB" /> The maneuver was first identified as the Kenobi Offensive and its nature detailed in [[The Truce at Bakura Sourcebook|''The Truce at Bakura Sourcebook'']] guide for [[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game|''Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game'']], which was written by Tyers and [[Eric S. Trautmann]], being published in [[1996]].<ref name="TTABS" /> The Kenobi Offensive was confirmed to have been created for use during the Clone Wars via an entry in [[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia|''The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia'']], which was published in [[2008]] and written by a group of authors led by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]] and [[Pablo Hidalgo]].<ref name="TCSWE">[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia|''The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia'']]</ref>

